/wiki/2010_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The 2010 European Track Championships were the inaugural elite European Track Championships in track cycling and took place at the BGŻ Arena in Pruszków, Poland, between 5 and 7 November.
/wiki/Tim_Veldt: Tim Veldt (born 14 February 1984) is a Dutch track cyclist. During his career Veldt won two world cup classics in the team sprint, two European titles (under 23 1 km time trial and omnium) as well as three Dutch national titles (1 km time trial twice and keirin). During the 2005 UCI Track Cycling World Championships he won the silver medal in the team sprint together with Theo Bos and Teun Mulder.
/wiki/2010_European_Track_Championships_: The Men's omnium was one of the 6 men's events at the 2010 European Track Championships, held in Pruszków, Poland.
/wiki/Levi_Heimans: Levi Heimans (born 24 July 1985 in Diemen, North Holland) is a Dutch track cyclist.
/wiki/Arno_van_der_Zwet: Arno van der Zwet (born 7 May 1986) is a track cyclist from Netherlands. In 2010 he won the bronze medal in the team pursuit at the 2010 UEC European Track Championships in Pruszków, Poland.
/wiki/Sipke_Zijlstra: Sipke Zijlstra (born 13 April 1985) is a track cyclist from Netherlands. He participated in the team pursuit at the 2009 and 2010 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. In the under-23 category he won the bronze medal in the team pursuit at the 2007 UEC European Track Championships. In 2010 he won the bronze medal in the team pursuit at the 2010 UEC European Track Championships, together with Levi Heimans, Arno van der Zwet and Tim Veldt in Pruszków, Poland.
/wiki/2010_European_Track_Championships_: The Men's Team Pursuit was one of the 6 men's events at the 2010 European Track Championships, held in Pruszków, Poland.
/wiki/2011_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The 2011 European Track Championships was the second edition of the elite European Track Championships in track cycling and took place at the Omnisport Arena in Apeldoorn, Netherlands, between 21 and 23 October.
/wiki/Kirsten_Wild: Kirsten Carlijn Wild (born 15 October 1982) is a Dutch professional racing cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Women's Continental Team Ceratizit–WNT Pro Cycling. Wild competed in two track cycling events at the 2012 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/2011_European_Track_Championships_: The Women's omnium was held on 22–23 October 2011. 18 riders participated over six competitions.
/wiki/2013_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The 2013 UEC European Track Championships was the fourth edition of the elite UEC European Track Championships in track cycling and took place at the Omnisport Arena in Apeldoorn, Netherlands, between 18 and 20 October. The Event was organised by the European Cycling Union.
/wiki/Elis_Ligtlee: Elis Ligtlee (born 28 June 1994) is a Dutch track cyclist. She represented her nation at the 2014 and 2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. She won the gold medal in the Keirin race at the 2016 Summer Olympics. Following her Olympic victory, Ligtlee was officially inducted to the Knight of the Order of Orange-Nassau.
/wiki/Dion_Beukeboom: Dion Beukeboom (born 2 February 1989) is a Dutch racing cyclist. He rode at the 2013 UCI Road World Championships.
/wiki/Roy_Eefting: Roy Eefting (born 4 September 1989) is a Dutch road and track cyclist. He competed at the 2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships.
/wiki/Jenning_Huizenga: Jenning Huizenga (born 29 March 1984, in Franeker) is a Dutch professional racing cyclist.
/wiki/2014_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The 2014 UEC European Track Championships was the fifth edition of the elite UEC European Track Championships in track cycling and took place at the Vélodrome Amédée Détraux in Baie-Mahault, Guadeloupe, France, between 16 and 19 October. The Event was organised by the European Cycling Union. All European champions are awarded the UEC European Champion jersey which may be worn by the champion throughout the year when competing in the same event at other competitions.
/wiki/Matthijs_Buchli: Matthijs Büchli (born 13 December 1992) is a Dutch track cyclist.
/wiki/Shanne_Braspennincx: Shanne Braspennincx (born 18 May 1991) is a Dutch female track cyclist. She competed at the 2014 and 2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships.
/wiki/2015_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The 2015 UEC European Track Championships was the sixth edition of the elite UEC European Track Championships in track cycling and took place at the Velodrome Suisse in Grenchen, Switzerland, between 14 and 18 October. The Event was organised by the European Cycling Union. All European champions are awarded the UEC European Champion jersey which may be worn by the champion throughout the year when competing in the same event at other competitions.
/wiki/Nils_van_%27t_Hoenderdaal: Nils van 't Hoenderdaal (born 3 October 1993) is a Dutch track cyclist.
/wiki/Jeffrey_Hoogland: Jeffrey Hoogland (born 16 March 1993) is a Dutch track cyclist. He represented his nation in three editions of the 2013, 2014 and 2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. At the 2015 UEC European Track Championships, he collected a total of three gold medals, individually in the sprint and the 1 km time trial, and with Nils van 't Hoenderdaal and Hugo Haak in the team sprint.
/wiki/Hugo_Haak: Hugo Haak (born 29 October 1991) is a Dutch track cyclist. He represented his nation at the 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014 and 2015 UCI Track Cycling World Championships. At the 2016 UCI Track Cycling World Championships he won the silver medal in the team sprint.
/wiki/2015_UEC_European_Track_Championsh: The Men's team sprint was held on 15 October 2015.
The Men's sprint was held on 16 October 2015.
The Women's sprint was held on 16 October 2015.
The Men's 1 km time trial was held on 17 October 2015.
The Women's keirin was held on 18 October 2015.
The Women's 500 m time trial  was held on 17 October 2015.
